Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is backpropagation?
AI Response

Backpropagation computes gradients of the loss with respect to each weight by applying the chain rule
backwards through the network, enabling weight updates via gradient descent.

Example 1.2

User

What is a transformer model?
AI Response

A transformer is a deep learning architecture using self-attention mechanisms that process all tokens in
parallel, enabling efficient NLP. GPT and BERT are transformer-based models.

Example 1.3

User

What is a confusion matrix?
AI Response

A confusion matrix shows counts of true/false positives and negatives for a classifier, enabling computation of
accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 score.

Example 1.4

User

What is deep learning?
AI Response

Deep learning is a subset of machine learning that uses multi-layered neural networks to learn
representations of data. It excels at tasks like image recognition, NLP, and speech synthesis.

Example 1.5

User

What is gradient descent?
AI Response

Gradient descent is an optimization algorithm that iteratively adjusts model parameters in the direction
opposite to the gradient of the loss function to find a minimum.

Example 1.6

User

What is a GAN?
AI Response

A Generative Adversarial Network pits a generator (creates fake data) against a discriminator (identifies
fakes), training each other until the generator produces realistic data.

Example 1.7

User

What is attention mechanism?
AI Response



Attention allows a model to focus on relevant input parts during output generation. Self-attention in
transformers computes weighted relationships between all token pairs.

Example 1.8

User

What is reinforcement learning?
AI Response

Reinforcement learning trains an agent to make decisions by interacting with an environment and receiving
rewards or penalties, aiming to maximize cumulative reward over time.

Example 1.9

User

What is the softmax function?
AI Response

Softmax converts a vector of raw scores (logits) into probabilities that sum to 1, typically used as the final
activation in multi-class classification models.

Example 1.10

User

What is a neural network?
AI Response

A neural network is a series of algorithms modeled after the human brain, consisting of input, hidden, and
output layers, with weights adjusted during training to minimize prediction error.



